act.article:
2 Definitions. In these rules, unless the context 
otherwise requires, 


a Act means the Electricity Act, 2003; 

b Appellate Tribunal means the Appellate Tribunal for Electricity 
  established under Section 110 of the Act; 

c Chairperson means the Chairperson the Appellate Tribunal appointed 
  under section 113 of the Act; 

d Member means a Member of the Appellate Tribunal appointed 
  under section 113 of the Act; 

e Words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the 
  Act shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Act.
